<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-296-974  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 296 974.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Systems News  April 2 1990 n461 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Mainframe confusion. (IBM marketing dilemma)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Sperling, Ed.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>IBM is sending mixed messages to its larger customers about thenature of the next generation of mainframe products.andP;  Confusionexists about whether the new products will be decidedly fasterthan current ones or just the same processor in a new cabinet.andP;  Adebate is raging over whether to add fiber-optic technology to the3090 J or simply transfer the technology of the J model to a newcabinet, enhance it somewhat and market it as a faster, smaller,more energy-efficient system.andP;  Industry observers say the'beef-and-sizzle' conflict is between the company's EnterpriseSystems group, which is touting the virtues of fiber optics, andmarketing officials.andP;  Customers are hearing different stories andthe conflict, which could not come at a worse time, may have aparalyzing effect on the vendor.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (marketing).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Product:   IBM 3090 J (Mainframe computer) (marketing).andO;Topic:     Marketing StrategyMainframe ComputersProduct DevelopmentCustomer RelationsFiber Optics.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>